<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-11-0398 </DOCNO><TEXT>Spain has always suffered from lack of organisation in coal research anddevelopment, with a 'hotch-potch' of research centres, sometimes unclearobjectives and inadequate resources. With only limited financial means,no system to coordinate these resources and no coherent programme toprovide for the needs of the coal industry, positive results have understandablybeen few. It is only work by a few individual organisations that hasachieved relevant results. The managing organisation for technologicalcoal research and development (OCICARBON) was thus created with the aimof managing, promoting and financing technological research and developmenton subjects connected with coal. This article describes the work andaims of the Association.</TEXT></DOC>